==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lumper
<hw>Lump"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Lamper
eel</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The European eelpout; -- called
also <altname>lumpen</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lumper</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Lumper
<hw>Lump"er</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
lumps.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A laborer who is employed to load or unload vessels
when in harbor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lumpfish</ent>⟦br⟧
